The only choice I had,

778
02:09:17,916 --> 02:09:20,384
the only thing I could control...

779
02:09:22,221 --> 02:09:24,985
was when and how...

780
02:09:25,057 --> 02:09:27,423
and where that was gonna happen.

781
02:09:27,526 --> 02:09:29,551
So...

782
02:09:31,096 --> 02:09:33,155
I made a rope.

783
02:09:35,234 --> 02:09:38,328
And I went up to the summit
to hang myself.

784
02:09:41,707 --> 02:09:43,971
But I had to test it, you know?

785
02:09:44,042 --> 02:09:46,772
Of course. You know me.

786
02:09:48,781 --> 02:09:54,083
And the weight of the log
snapped the limb of the tree.

787
02:09:54,153 --> 02:09:58,852
So I... I couldn't even kill myself
the way I wanted to.

788
02:09:58,924 --> 02:10:01,620
I had power over nothing.

789
02:10:10,369 --> 02:10:14,305
And that's when this feeling came
over me like a warm blanket.

790
02:10:17,910 --> 02:10:22,347
I knew, somehow...

791
02:10:22,414 --> 02:10:24,848
that I had to stay alive.

792
02:10:26,351 --> 02:10:28,285
Somehow.

793
02:10:29,388 --> 02:10:31,856
I had to keep breathing,

794
02:10:34,126 --> 02:10:36,993
even though there was no reason
to hope.

795
02:10:38,497 --> 02:10:42,433
And all my logic said that I would
never see this place again.

796
02:10:47,005 --> 02:10:49,064
So that's what I did.

797
02:10:49,975 --> 02:10:52,307
I stayed alive.

798
02:10:52,411 --> 02:10:54,436
I kept breathing.

799
02:10:56,281 --> 02:10:59,079
Then one day
that logic was proven all wrong,

800
02:10:59,151 --> 02:11:05,579
because the tide came in,
gave me a sail.

801
02:11:10,195 --> 02:11:12,220
And now, here I am.

802
02:11:15,534 --> 02:11:19,561
I'm back...in Memphis,

803
02:11:19,638 --> 02:11:21,697
talking to you.

804
02:11:23,308 --> 02:11:25,742
I have ice in my glass.

805
02:11:32,551 --> 02:11:35,019
And I've lost her all over again.

806
02:11:42,461 --> 02:11:45,328
I'm so sad that I don't have Kelly.

807
02:11:50,302 --> 02:11:54,033
But I'm so grateful that
she was with me on that island.

808
02:12:00,879 --> 02:12:03,370
And I know what I have to do now.

809
02:12:05,951 --> 02:12:07,976
I gotta keep breathing.

810
02:12:10,522 --> 02:12:12,990
Because tomorrow, the sun will rise.

811
02:12:14,359 --> 02:12:17,021
Who knows what the tide could bring?

812
02:12:30,842 --> 02:12:33,310
# I gave a letter to the postman

813
02:12:34,413 --> 02:12:36,438
# He put it in his sack

814
02:12:38,216 --> 02:12:41,344
# Bright and early next mornin'

815
02:12:41,453 --> 02:12:44,183
# He brought my letter back

816
02:12:44,256 --> 02:12:45,883
# She wrote upon it

817
02:12:45,958 --> 02:12:47,983
# Return to sender

818
02:12:49,294 --> 02:12:51,319
# Address unknown

819
02:12:53,565 --> 02:12:55,590
# No such number... #

820
02:13:22,461 --> 02:13:24,395
Hello!

821
02:13:28,800 --> 02:13:30,427
Hello!

822
02:13:36,241 --> 02:13:38,368
(Whistles )

823
02:13:38,443 --> 02:13:40,707
FedEx!

824
02:14:47,846 --> 02:14:49,677
You look lost.

825
02:14:49,748 --> 02:14:51,409
I do?

826
02:14:51,483 --> 02:14:53,747
Where are you headed?

827
02:14:56,922 --> 02:14:59,390
Well, I was just about
to figure that out.

828
02:15:00,492 --> 02:15:02,323
Well, that's 83 South.

829
02:15:02,427 --> 02:15:07,490
And this road here
will hook you up with I-40 East.

830
02:15:07,566 --> 02:15:09,591
If you turn right,

831
02:15:09,668 --> 02:15:13,570
that'll take you to
Amarillo, Flagstaff,

832
02:15:13,638 --> 02:15:15,606
California.

833
02:15:16,675 --> 02:15:18,700
And if you head back that direction,

834
02:15:18,777 --> 02:15:22,508
you'll find a whole lotta nothin'
all the way to Canada.

835
02:15:23,982 --> 02:15:25,813
I got it.

836
02:15:25,884 --> 02:15:27,943
All right, then.

837
02:15:30,522 --> 02:15:32,513
Good luck, cowboy.

838
02:15:32,591 --> 02:15:34,456
Thank you.
